        It is a shame an average side has made it to the final because of the way the groups finished. It was primarily the failure of Spain and England to win their groups which caused such a disparity between the 2 halves of the draw but allowing 3rd placed teams hasn't helped. Some will say it has "made" the tournament but all it has "made" is it weaker. Portugal should've gone after the group stages and I don't think any neutrals would've argued against it. All 6 3rd placed teams are/were poor. Croatia have 1 terrible game in the tournament and are out whereas Portugal have had 90 minutes of good football in the whole tournament and have made the final. Italy, had they made the final, would've had to play- Belgium, Spain, Germany and France. For them, ironically, the final would most likely had been the easiest game they played all tournament! Essentially, Portugal haven't made it to the final on merit, they have made it by default and that is embarrassing for the tournament imho.
